cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a regularizer for deep neural networks to induce low-rank representations, which improves the robustness of the models to input perturbations. The paper also conducts experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it evaluates the robustness of the models to adversarial and random noise. 

The paper's focus on improving the robustness of deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Lastly, the paper's potential impact on security and privacy, as it improves the robustness of models to adversarial attacks, suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
